(169, 1, '2015-03-05 22:00:23', '2015-03-05 22:00:23', '<h1><b>Key Facts</b></h1>\r\n<b>Team size supported: </b>80 teammates\r\n\r\n<b>Locations: America, HQ </b>Sunnyvale, CA\r\n\r\n<b>Industry: </b>FinTech\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><b>The Word </b><b> </b></h2>\r\n<blockquote><b>“</b>The Avenue Code team in Brazil was very knowledgeable on the best QA practices. They provided detailed explanations of the problems found, which allowed us to quickly fix the bugs. It was all very simple. Especially leveraging the near-shore shared timezone between teams.”</blockquote>\r\n- <b>Peter Nguyen, </b>Digital Marketing Manager\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><b>Background</b></h2>\r\nStartups are Agile - they have to be when dealing with a constantly changing environment. PayNearMe was no exception. They provide an electronic cash payment system that allows businesses and government agencies to collect cash payments remotely at local stores such as 7-Eleven and Family Dollar. How PayNearMe works:\r\n\r\n1. Get the PayCode\r\n\r\nIf the biller or service provider offers PayNearMe as a payment option, they will send a PayCode via email or text message. They may also send a printed bill or a card with the PayNearMe PayCode.\r\n\r\n2. Go to a nearby payment location\r\n\r\nVisit a nearby payment location and present the PayNearMe PayCode to the cashier, along with the cash. PayNearMe is accepted at over 17,000 7-Eleven, Family Dollar, and ACE Cash Express stores nationwide.\r\n\r\n3. Pay with cash and get a receipt\r\n\r\nThe cashier scans the PayNearMe PayCode, accepts the cash, and provides a receipt as proof of payment. The biller gets notified immediately. The whole process takes less than a minute!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><b>The challenge</b></h2>\r\nIn order for PayNearMe to achieve their business goals - instantaneous and convenient access to cash - their online presence needs to be top priority. Achieving their business goals was dependent on creating a website that could support their customer base in real-time that was also responsive and mobile-friendly. However, when PayNearMe came to Avenue Code, their resources were allocated to other projects, so they needed an external team to take charge of their web project. In this project, they needed a modern looking and fully responsive website. Creating a Wordpress site that was responsive, elegant, and functional on all devices across all operating systems was only possible with the assistance of a swift, and knowledgeable team.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><b>The Journey </b></h2>\r\nAvenue Code joined PayNearMe and we were able to provide them with QA guidance. Our QA team provided the proper testing to ensure their site was everything they desired. We helped them find hidden bugs, and lay them to rest. PayNearMe needed everything done in lightening speed. With 30 percent of US consumers preferring cash as a tender, PayNearMe’s web presence is now able to bring cash payments into the 21st century with ease, by bridging the digital divide and allowing everyone to participate in the digital economy on PayNearMe’s responsive, mobile friendly website.', 'Case study: PayNearMe', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'case-study-paynearme', '', '', '2015-05-18 17:12:43', '2015-05-18 17:12:43', '', 0, 'http://localhost/acnew/?p=169', 0, 'post', '', 0),
