(253, 1, '2015-05-12 20:49:30', '2015-05-12 20:49:30', 'Lean Principles (come from Toyota Production System / Kanban - meaning "billboard") focus on elimination of waste (just in time production, replenishment triggered by demand), no iterations, switch tasking is minimized by setting work limits. Production is driven directly by customer demand -- close interaction with customers. Anything that does not generate immediate customer value is not being worked on. The goal is to improve by amplifying learning, eliminate constrains, empower the team while making decisions as late as possible.\r\n\r\nAgile is a framework for various methodologies: scrum, xp, pair. The Agile Manifesto (2001) was drafted by 17 software developers who got together at a Utah ski resort and agreed on the governing principles.\r\n\r\nIt is important to understand that Agile is a style of working, a mentality. <strong>We are not doing agile, but rather we are being agile.</strong>\r\n\r\nThe focus is on iterative, time boxed activity cycles and planning. No task limits are stated but rather team capacity measurements dictate the burn rate and productivity potential. Agile values people over process or tools and promotes co-location (business/customer and developers sit together), self organized teams, trusting the team, continuous integration, sustainability and adaptability (response to change) to build discipline. Team roles are also an important component of this practice. All this creates a cultural transition.\r\n\r\nLean Startup Concept is Eric Ries'' philosophy that focuses on creating a minimum viable product (unfinished product). It has nothing to do with funding or raising capital! To achieve this startups must eliminate waste (no lengthy business plans but rather a prototype or pitch) and focus on customer value using key performance indicators and a continuous deployment process."\r\n\r\nHow have these methodologies helped  your projects and organizations?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBy: Valerie Muravitsky\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Lean and Agile', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '246-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-05-12 20:49:30', '2015-05-12 20:49:30', '', 246, 'http://localhost/acnew/246-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(254, 1, '2013-07-17 21:34:56', '2013-07-17 21:34:56', 'Thursday January 17, some Avenue Coders had the opportunity to attend Source 13 hosted by Flurry.  There were over 600 people in attendance and the event attracted some of the most influential voices within the mobile community.\r\n\r\nA constant theme within the conference was the idea that mobile is increasingly a central part in the way that consumers interact with organizations. It was exciting to hear from founders and directors of companies who were already successful in the “mobile-first economy.”  They shared their insight as to what made their company a success.\r\n\r\nI personally appreciated Jason Spero’s presentation on “Winning with mobile in a multi-screen world,” which essentially talked about the concept of Omni-channel strategy. One analogy Jason gave was the following: A customer uses a mobile app to find a nearest location of a shoe store. The customer tries on the actual shoes and finds it fitting and very attractive. However, he’s walking out of the store empty-handed. Later, at home, he’s browsing the same shoe with the right size from a website that provides the lowest price.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/pic.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-197" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/pic-300x225.png" alt="pic" width="300" height="225" /></a>\r\n\r\nHere, the customer just used three screens to make the final purchase. Jason calls this, “Winning with mobile in a multi-screen world,” and Avenue Code calls this Omni-channel.\r\n\r\nAvenue Code has been talking about omni-channel for awhile and has been predicting what is happening now in the mobile-first world. We see that mobile is one of the biggest channels that the business should tap into and Avenue Code, known as an expert at Omni-channel, can definitely deliver that.\r\n\r\nWe believe that the established industry should not only create Mobile apps for the sake of having an app existing in app stores, but also create a good one. Performance does matter and Avenue Code delivers quality. Jessica Scorpio, the founder of Getaround, would probably agree with us because she said, “To disrupt [the industry you are in], the [mobile] app needs to work. Performance matters.”\r\n\r\nWe also believe that the client should create the mobile apps that takes most advantage of each and different platform. We were pleased to find out that Mike Ghaffary, VP of Business Dvelopment at Yelp shared the same opinion: “iPhone users and iPad users have very different user behaviors...so create iPad app differently.”\r\n\r\nSimon Khalaf, CEO of Flurry said, “Mobile is disrupting the payment system and it is worldwide phenomena.” I was pleased to hear this assuring message because Avenue Code has already started to revolutionize the world of mbanking working on platforms that allow consumers to pay utilizing their cell phones. Avenue Code understands that mobile capabilities will largely impact the future of financial institutions.\r\n\r\nOverall, I would say that the conference assured and proved Avenue Code’s vision and direction on technology-driven business. I hope to attend more of such great knowledge sharing conferences!', 'Avenue Code’s Response to Source13: Mobile First', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'avenue-codes-response-to-source13-mobile-first', '', '', '2015-05-18 17:20:49', '2015-05-18 17:20:49', '', 0, 'http://localhost/acnew/?p=254', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(255, 1, '2012-12-12 21:33:17', '2012-12-12 21:33:17', 'It''s Christmas, and through the great magic that surrounds this time of year, it awakens within us the potential for solidarity and compassion, it refills our spirit with hope in humanity and generosity - giving back.\r\n\r\nAnd with this spirit, the Avenue Code is organizing a charity campaign to help Daycare in an underprivileged neighborhood Creche Terra Nova, Brazil. Every day there are more than 100 children of the neighborhood who attend this daycare center. Children of the center are between the ages of 11 months to 6 years.  At this daycare they can receive education, food and recreation, as well as information about hygiene, health and citizenship. The daycare also promotes integration of activities with parents and the community.\r\n\r\nThis Christmas, the children wrote letters to Santa Claus asking for toys, clothes, school supplies, among other wants and needs.  The Avenue Code team in Brazil are collaborating with donations and meeting the demands of the letters.\r\n\r\nWe are asking for your cooperation so that we can meet the requests of all children (buy toys, clothes and school supplies) and make their Christmas happier and complete.\r\n\r\nWe are going to deliver all the collected gifts and also make a little party in this Daycare Center on Dec 12th. If you are in the US, you can also collaborate by donating some money though this website:http://vakinha.com.br/VaquinhaP.aspx?e=181374\r\n\r\nAll the money collected will be used to buy the gifts. Check out the daycare’s website:http://www.crecheterranova.com.br/\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Avenue Code Giving Back', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'avenue-code-giving-back', '', '', '2015-05-18 17:21:02', '2015-05-18 17:21:02', '', 0, 'http://localhost/acnew/?p=255', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(256, 1, '2012-10-17 21:32:09', '2012-10-17 21:32:09', 'Avenue Code''s premiere networking event, TECH TIME, finally happened Tuesday evening,\r\n\r\nOctober 9th, at the Hub. Top-tier talent from various industries such as: retail, IT, and finance were in attendance. The room was packed and there was an air of excitement as individuals had the opportunity to mingle with fellow IT professionals. Here are some highlights from the event!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-179" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01-300x198.png" alt="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01.png" width="300" height="198" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe MC of the event was the one of Avenue Code''s outstanding employees and the president of the San Francisco Bay Area Chapter of Project Management Institute Elaine Law, who opened the event with a welcome message. Then Cloud Evangelist, Jim Ash , from HP Cloud shared the reasons to migrate to a public cloud and future capabilities of HP’s public cloud. Avenue Code was pleased to have HP Cloud sponsor the event.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/02.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-180" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/02-300x198.png" alt="02" width="300" height="198" /></a><a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/03.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-181" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/03-300x198.png" alt="03" width="300" height="198" /></a>\r\n\r\nSoon after, Zeo Solomon gave a presentation on the Omni-channel.  His speech was inspiring and brought a comedic angle to the evening''s event. Zeo''s genius analogy of the "18th camel", --which implied that Omni-channel technology is a magical solution for frustrations caused by having multiple channels--was repeated throughout the rest of the event.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/04.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-182" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/04-300x198.png" alt="04" width="300" height="198" /></a>\r\n\r\nZeo''s presentation was the perfect segue into the panel discussion, which was moderated by Elaine Law. Avenue Code was honored to have a great set of panel guests: Kari Friedman, Chip Overstreet, and Lance Wills. They brought valuable experience and hands-on market insights to the table and updated the attendees on what retail stores have been doing with the integration of multiple channels of revenue steam.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/05.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-183" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/05-300x198.png" alt="05" width="300" height="198" /></a>\r\n\r\nThere was great interest from the crowd in hearing the panel guests. Some of the audience members raised critical questions on how to integrate different channels seamlessly. Even after the 50 minute panel session, people lingered around to discuss more about the possibility of the new technology. From this, we can confidently say that Avenue Code''s Tech Time ended successfully!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/07.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-185" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/07-300x198.png" alt="07" width="300" height="198" /></a> <a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/06.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-184" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/06-300x198.png" alt="06" width="300" height="198" /></a>\r\n\r\nHopefully you will join us next time.  The next Tech Time topic and date will be announced soon. For those who came, thank you very much. See you at the next Tech Time!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'October''s Tech Time Recap', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'octobers-tech-time-recap', '', '', '2015-05-18 17:21:15', '2015-05-18 17:21:15', '', 0, 'http://localhost/acnew/?p=256', 0, 'post', '', 0),
